The Cinderteeth Mountains are a discontinuous volcanic arc running west to northeast. Tectonically coupled to a deep continental fault; seismic events far away can trigger sympathetic tremors here.
Original inhabitants: the Ventspeakers, highland people who read gas color, tremor rhythm, and vent sound as practical geology encoded in ritual. Their polished name-stones still mark vent mouths at high elevations.
The Spirebound Conclave built a sanctum in the Western Fold for isolated research. They embedded resonance crystals at fault intersections along the Bellspine ridge to monitor seismic precursors. When the Conclave collapsed, the crystals were never retrieved. Some still resonate in the deep rock.
The Ashfall catastrophe: eruptions sent continent-wide ash clouds that contaminated wells, poisoned streams, and devastated Kowloon's delta via the Ashfall Monsoon. Rakuen's cisterns and orchards were destroyed. Trade networks collapsed for years.
Six subregions: Ember Crown (active calderas, lethal glassfall), Bellspine (subsurface resonance disorients travelers), Chalkwind Saddles (only viable commercial transit route), Glasswash Fans (obsidian quarries, sulfur gardens), Blackstep Footholds (mountain law meets civic law), Western Fold (hidden Conclave ruins, still smoldering).
Route houses enforce Hazard Doctrine: Silent Bell Protocol (halt and disperse when resonance shifts), double-water doctrine (never mix hydration reserves, from the Ashblind Convoy Loss at the Dead Pools). These are codified survival law.
The Ash Cult claims eruptions are divine verdicts against civic corruption. This is a degraded echo of Ventspeaker doctrine, stripped of empirical rigor and loaded with apocalyptic meaning.
