Mafdet's Quarantine Ledger classifies the Cinderteeth as a Systemic Supply Chain Threat, Tier One. No other geographic feature has disrupted Mafdet's commerce as consistently.
The Ashfall wrote Mafdet's emergency protocols. Ash poisoned wells and streams, collapsing the inland trade network for years. Caravans stopped. The oasis corridor dried up of goods, not water. The harbor sat empty. The Sand-Sea Carters' Guild nearly dissolved during the second Ash Winter. Lesson: volcanic risk is supply chain risk. A western caldera eruption empties eastern docks three seasons later.
The Conclave's abandoned resonance crystals in the Bellspine are unattested artifacts of unknown function. No manifests were filed before the Conclave collapsed. Under the Dual-Attestation Protocol, any crystal fragment from the Cinderteeth requires Tier Three quarantine: inland provenance unverifiable, maritime risk classification high-unknown.
The Ventspeakers interest Mafdet's Harbor Wardens as a lost early-warning network. Their name-stones at vent mouths function as attestation markers, proof someone maintained a watching relationship with specific vents. That relationship is broken. No one reads the mountain with their rigor now.
Mountain route house Hazard Doctrine (Silent Bell Protocol, double-water doctrine) is sound logistics discipline. Mafdet's harbor chain operates on the same principles: when conditions change, halt, verify, proceed only under attestation. Both systems were learned from disaster.
The Ash Cult's claim that eruptions are divine verdicts is the kind of unattested assertion the Shrine of the First Claw was built to reject. The mountain does not judge. It erupts. The difference matters.
